      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make and chill the dough",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Beat {{unsalted-butter}} and {{caster-sugar}} until pale and fluffy, about 3 minutes. Add {{eggs}} one at a time, beating between each. Add {{vanilla-extract}}.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Sift in {{plain-flour}}, {{baking-powder}}, and {{sea-salt-fine}}. Mix until a smooth dough forms. Divide in half, flatten each half into a disc, wrap, and refrigerate for at least 1 hour.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Cut and bake",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Heat the oven to 170°C fan (190°C conventional). Line two trays with baking paper.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Roll one disc of dough on a lightly floured surface to 4 to 5 mm thick. Cut into shapes and place on the lined trays. Re-roll the trimmings and cut again.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Bake for 10 to 12 minutes until the edges are just starting to colour. The centres will look pale and underdone; they firm up as they cool. Transfer to a rack and cool completely before icing.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the royal icing and decorate",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Whisk {{egg-whites}} until frothy. Add {{icing-sugar}} and {{lemon-juice}} and beat until the icing is thick, white, and holds a stiff peak. Cover with cling film when not using; it sets quickly.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "To flood a biscuit: thin a portion of the icing with a few drops of water until it flows slowly off a spoon. Use a small spoon to spread it within the edges of the biscuit. Leave to set for at least 1 hour before adding piped details on top.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "intro": "Dough handling and icing consistency are the two things to watch.",
          "items": [
            {
              "fix": "Return the dough to the fridge for 10 minutes whenever it becomes sticky. Warm dough spreads; cold dough holds its outline.",
              "cause": "Dough too warm.",
              "symptom": "Cookies spreading and losing their shape."
            },
            {
              "fix": "Thin the flood icing a little more. Dry in a cool, stable environment rather than near a heat source.",
              "cause": "Icing too thick when applied, or dried too fast.",
              "symptom": "Royal icing cracking after it sets."
            }
          ],
          "heading": "Troubleshooting"
        }
      }
    ]
  },
